\begin_layout Subsection
Flexible and polarizable models
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Up to this point, molecules were considered as rigid bodies.
 Flexible models give extra degrees of freedom in vibration and internal
 rotation.
 In that case, the interaction potential contains several extra terms, yielding
 typically five kinds of forces: three for the direct interactions in addition
 to the two indirect interactions (LJ and Coulomb).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
placement h
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
